  "observation": "Brainstorm triggered by plateau. 4 proposals generated.",
  "suggestion": "The plateau is caused by fitness landscape convergence: the current architecture has pushed organisms toward a single optimal morphology/behavior that exploits the composite fitness function. This is evolutionary success, but it's a local maximum. Escape requires either (1) making the landscape non-stationary (predators), (2) fragmenting the landscape into multiple peaks (tissue specialization), or (3) redefining fitness to reward diversity of solutions rather than convergence to one (pareto ranking). The system has optimized beauty given current constraints—now it needs new constraints.; [medium] Multi-tissue differentiation with metabolic specialization. Add 3-4 tissue types (muscle, skin, nerve, storage) with distinct energy costs and beauty contributions. Allow organisms to allocate cell budget across tissue types rather than treating all cells homogeneously. Tissues express different phenotypes (muscle = speed, skin = color/pattern/luminosity, nerve = decision complexity, storage = survival buffer). — Current architecture likely converged on 'average' organisms. Tissue differentiation creates orthogonal axes for specialization—some organisms become sprinters (high muscle), others become artists (high skin beauty), others become thinkers (high nerve). This breaks the single-peak fitness landscape and allows diverse evolutionary paths to coexist at high fitness.; [hard] Dynamic predator-prey relationship tier. Introduce a second agent type (predators) that hunt organisms. Predator fitness = success rate at catching prey. Prey organisms that are currently 'optimal' become vulnerable (predators evolve to hunt them), forcing constant arms-race evolution. Predator and prey populations co-evolve, continuously reshaping the fitness landscape. — Plateau occurs when fitness landscape is static—organisms optimize and stagnate. Adding adversarial selection pressure (predators) makes the landscape non-stationary: yesterday's optimal solution is tomorrow's target. This forces continuous innovation rather than convergence.; [easy] Pareto-frontier evaluation instead of composite fitness. Replace single fitness = 0.5*survival + 0.3*beauty + 0.2*efficiency with multi-objective ranking. Evaluate organisms on survival, beauty, and efficiency independently. Selection favors organisms on the pareto frontier (non-dominated solutions). Allow multiple 'specialist' genotypes to coexist: beauty-maxed, survival-maxed, efficiency-maxed, and mixed strategies. — Composite fitness forces all organisms toward the same compromise point. Pareto ranking allows genuine diversity—a pure beauty specialist can coexist with a pure survival specialist if neither dominates the other. Evolution now explores the entire frontier rather than converging to one point, unlocking new solutions.",
